race.comment: BACK TO BONDI (5) got the job done last start after getting every chance in the run, winning by 0.5L. Out in trip again looks ideal for him, though where he gets to from the barrier is the query. He looks a nice gelding on the rise however and he can go back-to-back. MISTRESS OF WAR (3) made it back-to-back wins last start at this track and trip, sitting on the speed and scoring by 1L. She may be able to dictate from the front once again as she draw low  and she continues to raise the bar. Can extend her winning run. ROSIE CAN RUN (9) hasn't been far away in recent efforts, beaten 1.5L last time out over the mile. Out to 1800m today and although she may get back in the run, she can be finishing strongly. CHEYNE BAY (1) is third-up here and looks to be nearing his peak. Getting out in trip is a big tick and he's sure to be in the finish. VENUS KING (6) is third-up here and with the aid of an inside draw, he can be in the finish.
